UID:uqHgrlJHtD9pFWChOl-Ef
SUMMARY:Seattle: Mt. Baker Park
DTSTAMP:20260315T214149Z
DTSTART:20260318T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Mount Baker Park. \\nJo
	in EarthCorps and Green Seattle Partnership as we work to create a healthi
	er forest in Mt Baker Park! Mt. Baker Park is located along a green boulev
	ard that heads down to a bathing beach on Lake Washington. Situated in a r
	esidential neighborhood\\\, this park has become a community gathering pla
	ce where people enjoy the many amenities of this park as well as its urban
	 forest. The forest of Mt. Baker Park is being threatened by plant species
	 such as ivy and blackberry. These plants take over parts of the forest by
	 overgrowing and choking native vegetation. Join us as we work to get thes
	e species under control and keep the native plants thriving! \\nRegister t
	o meet.\n\nhttps://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/seattle-mt-baker-p
	ark/\n\nFrom The Seattle Parks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/seattle-mt-baker-park/
